						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 16th century.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift to a god by Ēchami-nāyaka and another gift to <hi rend="italic">Kula karaṇi</hi> Tiṁmarasa. The record is damaged.</p>						

